Thank you for your interest in contributing!



About contributing

We appreciate suggestions to improve the code and resolve bug fixes, but please be respectful and follow the code of conduct.



How to contribute

  1. On your GitHub account, fork the package repository.


  1. Clone your fork of the repository to your local machine using a Command Line Interface tool.

git clone https://github.com/PATH-TO-YOUR-FORKED-REPOSITORY


  1. Navigate to the directory containing the R package on your machine.


  1. Install the dependencies listed in DESCRIPTION.

Rscript -e 'devtools::install_deps()'


  1. Install the package locally for development purposes.

R CMD INSTALL .


  1. Start contributing!



Making a Pull Request

  1. Ensure your code runs correctly and is well documented.


  1. Create a pull request.

git add <modified-file>
git commit -m "Some descriptive message about your change"
git push origin <your-branch-name>


  1. Someone from our team will review your changes and decide whether to add this to the main code.
